desc: A blue whale's heart is so large that a human can swim through its arteries. The blue whale is the largest animal ever known to have lived on Earth, and its heart can weigh as much as 1,300 pounds (about 590 kilograms) and is roughly the size of a small car. The aorta, which is the main artery, is so large that a human child could swim through it. #interesting #hearth #whale

desc: The orca whale, also known as the killer whale, is one of the most fantastic and intelligent predators in the oceans. Its spectacular leaps out of the water are not only beautiful to watch—they can be used for communication, parasite removal, a display of strength, or even as part of hunting strategies. With its striking black and white body and imposing dorsal fin, the orca glides through the water with agility and precision, revealing a majestic and dominant presence. . When hunting, the orca demonstrates why it is considered one of nature's most efficient animals. It feeds on a variety of prey, including fish, seals, squid, and even dolphins and other whales. They hunt in family groups called pods, where each member plays a specific role, using coordinated tactics and sophisticated vocal communication. Some populations specialize in certain types of prey, and there are records of orcas pursuing dolphins with speed and strategy, surrounding them and attacking with precision.  It is a combination of strength, intelligence and cooperation that makes the orca a true queen of the seas. #creatorsearchinsights #ocean #whale #nature #love

desc: We took this exact tour 4 years ago to the day. Our minds were blown then and we are again leaving this area in complete awe. The tours here promise you nothing other than taking a boat out into this protected lagoon to whale watch. The lagoon is protected within the Vizcaíno Biosphere Reserve UNESCO World Heritage site. Gray whales come to Baja to spend about three months (February to April) enjoying the warm water lagoons along the peninsula’s coast to mate, give birth and raise their young. Before you even leave the dock you’ll see whales spouting, and huge splashes from whales breaching in the distance. Once you’re far enough out in the lagoon, the captain will cut the engine and sometimes the whales will choose to come up to interact with these small boats and the people on them. There is nothing drawing them in to us, and they are not being chased, it’s completely up to them to create this interaction. It’s an unbelievable sight, and a surreal experience—something that takes a moment to process as you’re eye to eye with a gray whale. #fyp #graywhale #bajamexico

desc: Don’t worry, it looked like this baby humpback whale just ate someone… but it’s all about the camera angle! Humpback whales couldn’t actually swallow a human even if they tried. Their throats are only about the size of a grapefruit. These gentle giants are filter feeders, opening wide to scoop up fish & krill, then pushing the water back out through their baleen plates. So while it might look like someone just got gulped, the only thing on the menu is a buffet of tiny fish and plankton! 🐋 #whale #humpbackwhale #swimwithwhales #ocean #snorkeling
